    <stitle>2 SPEED AND DOUBLE REDUCTION SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - IDENTIFICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>IDENTIFICATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
            <title>AXLE</title>
            <para>Axle and differential carrier identification is either stamped on the carrier itself or on a metal tag
                affixed to the carrier (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401601">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Location on the carrier is the same.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401601" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401601" filename="../figg14/g1401601.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Axle Identification</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The complete axle is identified by the specification number stamped on the rear right hand side of the
                axle housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401602">Figure 2</hotlnk>). This number identifies all component parts of the axle as
                built by Eaton, including special OEM requirements such as yoke or flange.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401602" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401602" filename="../figg14/g1401602.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Axle Identification</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>In addition, some axles may include a metal identification tag.</para>
            <para>This tag only identifies the housing. It does not identify the differential carrier assembly
                components.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
